summary:
Gwelda Armor Pack contains three armors. Vampire, Dawnguard and Witch.
All have a variety of customization options from trousers, socks, stockings, hoods,cloaks to different color combinations to hair.
descriptionHtml:
[center][color=#EBF1DD][size=4][i][font=Times New Roman]
[img]http://static-2.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1408009524.jpg[/img]
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Important information![/b]

The HDT version of the mod requires [b]HDT High Heels System[/b]. Get it [b][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36213/?]here[/url][/b]!
This mod does [b]NOT[/b] require Dawnguard expansion.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Info:[/b]

Gwelda Armor Pack contains three armors. Vampire, Dawnguard and Witch. All have a variety of customization options from trousers, socks, stockings, hoods to different color combinations to hair. Vampire and Witch are cloth armors and Dawnguard is light with stats equal to dragonscale.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[youtube]keWA6ypUXr4[/youtube] [youtube]ri0xfmR0x4M[/youtube]
[youtube]K8qRmnbWVzw[/youtube]
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[youtube]S8Y43mCj9Pk[/youtube] [youtube]1aIHrCBDdTo[/youtube]
[youtube]xwni1ryNKZg[/youtube] [youtube]LcEaSBqEnUg[/youtube]

Thank you!
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Notes:[/b]

This is the second mod of a series that will contain eight armors with three variations each. I came up with the idea when I saw the Minidresses Collection mod by Tiwa44 who did an awesome job converting some of the long dresses to mini versions. So I started experimenting with his meshes to see if it's possible to convert them into mini armors [b]- actually they are turning out to be full armors ^^ -[/b] and I came up with some very creative results.

These armors will not offer any protection in real life so don't use them at home!

There is no guarantee that I will finish all the armors but the creation has been fun so far and as long as I'm excited about this project I'll keep working on it until hopefully all armors are complete. [b]- A big THANK YOU here to all of you guys that endorsed,commented or just played and keep playing using my previous mods! -[/b]

Below are the eight different mini dresses by Tiwa44 and the progress I'm making with the armors. I'll update the image every time something major changes. Also I came up with the names (with the help of a generator) and to my knowledge they are not used by anyone else.

[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/61012-1-1442736357.jpg[/img]

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Acquisition:[/b]
If for any reason you can't find the box try typing "help gwelda" and "player.additem xxxxxxxx 1" in the console to get the armor pieces manually.
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-2-1405232090.jpg[/img]
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Versions:[/b]
1.01 Very small tweaks to the hair transparency to correct a small issue I noticed and an adjustment to Sapphire and Sick Frog colors to make them a bit darker.
1.00 Release

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Optional Downloads:[/b]

- A barefoot version that doesn't require HDT but does not contain the boots. Sorry about that but I designed the armors with high heels in mind and it was impossible for me to find any flat boots that could fit to my concept.

- A light armor conversion for both Vampire and Witch armors in case you are the fighter type.

- A medium resolution texture replacer in case the main version have an impact on the performance or in case you are using all three armors at once by equipping them to followers.

- A low resolution texture replacer for weaker pcs 1024 pixels max. <3 :)

- Bigger hoods in case you experience clipping issues with the head.

- German Translation

For all the above the main file is required, to install just overwrite the files.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]External Downloads:[/b]

A beautiful CBBE conversion!
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/58873/?]Gwelda Armor Pack - CBBE - HDT BodySlide TBBP[/url] by Mitosuke

[b]UNPB BBP -> [/b] [url=http://robton.nu/]UNPB BBP version by Robton[/url]

The non-HDT version of the mod is also included in:
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/24684/?]UNP Clothing Merchants[/url] by Foaman
Many thanks!

A great replacer mod for the female soldiers:
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/57988/?]Gwelda Armor Pack - Dawnguard soldiers replacer - UNP[/url] by PeCool

7B HDT:
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/68512/?]7B HDT Gwelda Armor Pack Sevenbase Conversion by GameFever[/url]

UNPB:
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/69709/?]MiniArmorsCollection - UNPB by gutris1[/url]

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b][color=#C0504D]Required mods:[/color][/b]

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36213/?]HDT HighHeels System by hydrogensayshdt[/url] for the HDT version.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Known issues:[/b]
Using HDT Version without HDT High Heels System will cause your game to crash.
Due to the many transparencies of the armors, blood spills appear in places they shouldn't.
One workaround is to use the mod [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/60/?]Enhanced Blood Textures[/url] and set the wounds duration to a minimum.
If you are using HDT HighHeels System and you see weird numbers at the top left of your screen disable the debug info as shown bellow.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401335443.jpg[/img] [img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1405232089.jpg[/img]

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Installation:[/b]
a) Using the nexus mod manager
b) Manual by extracting the contents of the compressed file in the Skyrim/Data folder
[b]Important![/b] You can only have one of the two versions installed. If you want to switch between HDT and Non HDT then uninstall the one you are currently using.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Un-installation:[/b]
a) Using the nexus mod manager
b) Manual by deleting Gwelda Armor Pack.esp from the Skyrim/Data folder
and by deleting the folders that have the word [b]Gwelda[/b] inside the Skyrim/Data/Textures/DX/MiniArmorsCollection/ and Skyrim/Data/Meshes/DX/MiniArmorsCollection/ folders.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Mods used in the screenshots and video:[/b]
Body: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/6709/?]DIMONIZED UNP female body by dimon99[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/37900/?]UNP BLESSED BODY - UNPB by Blessed Redux Project team[/url]
Face: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/35474/?]The Ningheim Race by Seren4XX HelloSanta Urshi and co[/url]
Eyes: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/54416/?]Eye Normal Map Fix by Mr Dave[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/21232/?]Skyrim - Glowing Eyes v4 by dumle35[/url]
Textures: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/52841/?]Freckle Mania by tetrodoxin[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/28946/?]Sporty Sexy Sweat - wet body skin texture by Xs2reality[/url]
Hair: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/10168/?]ApachiiSkyHair by Apachii[/url]
Weapons: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/24909/?]aMidianBorn Book of Silence by CaBaL- EmeraldReign-the AMB team[/url]
Environment: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/141/?] Skyrim Flora Overhaul by vurt[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/1111/?]Pure Waters by Laast[/url]
ENB: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/30936/?]RealVision ENB by SkyrimTuner[/url] heavily modified :3

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Permissions[/b]
If you want to use any of the non vanilla meshes of this mod please credit/contact the original creators listed bellow. Anything else you can use freely as long as you credit my work in the comments.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Credits:[/b]
Armor meshes [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/47376/?]UNP Minidresses Collection by Tiwa44[/url]
Hair meshes [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/10168/?]ApachiiSkyHair by Apachii[/url]
Armlets, Bracers, Hood and Cloak meshes [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/18008/?]Ashara Princes of the Woods for UNP and male by SydneyB[/url]
Cuisse, socks, stockings, trousers mesh [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/24444/?]UNP Undies by Petrovich[/url]
Collar mesh [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/15529/?]R18Pn Set - Inner Wear Set for UNP and CBBEV3 by NPR[/url]
Boots mesh [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/43381/?]Bobs Boots for CBBE and UNP by Beazalbob69[/url]
Special thanks to malkaViana who gave me the idea to create trousers!

Many thanks to:

TKHBMVP for the German translation! [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/4827500/?tb=mods&pUp=1]Nexus Resources[/url], [url=http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=298040664] Steam Resources[/url]
